FBIS3-34728 "drnes030_p_94004" FBIS-NES-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Warring Sides Deny Official Cease-Fire in Effect LD1302185794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network in Persian 1630 GMT 13 Feb 94 LD1302185794 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Text] Reports from Kabul suggest that an unofficial cease-fire has come into effect there. This is at a time when the residents of Kabul face growing problems in connection with obtaining food. In the meantime, the warring sides in Afghanistan have rejected rumors that an official cease-fire has been announced in Kabul. One official from Rabbani's faction said: The current cease-fire is a result of bad weather, snow, and the month of Ramadan and it is not, in any way, an official cease-fire.
